gw.api.builder

Class AuditBuilder

  • java.lang.Object
    • gw.api.databuilder.DataBuilder<PolicyPeriod,AuditBuilder>
      • gw.api.builder.AuditBuilder
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ValueGenerator<PolicyPeriod>

    public class AuditBuilder
extends DataBuilder<PolicyPeriod,AuditBuilder>
    Builder for creating Audit periods. An Audit is a non-bound period. Simple usage of this builder is 
       new AuditBuilder().withAuditInformation(auditInformation).createAndCommit()
   new AuditBuilder().withAuditInformation(auditInformationBuilder).createAndCommit()
    AuditInformation is required; otherwise creation will fail.

    • Constructor Detail

      • AuditBuilder

        public AuditBuilder()
        Create an AuditBuilder, with default Status = QUOTED. The populator which handles Status runs at POSTPROCESS_PRIORITY_2. There is also a populator running at POSTPROCESS_PRIORITY_3 which handles CloseDate, UserAssignment and GroupAssignment.
